# Option Instead of Null (Hard Rule)

## Core Principles

1. **Option belongs in domain logic; null belongs at boundaries.** Use `Option<T>` in stores, lib, and services for absent-or-present semantics. Keep `string | null` in DTOs, wire formats, and DB rows.
2. **Match must produce a value; side-effects use `whenSome`/`whenRight`.** Use `Option.match`/`Either.match` only when both branches return a value (JSX, strings, booleans). For imperative fire-and-forget, use `whenSome(opt, fn)` or `whenRight(either, fn)` from `@/lib/optionHelpers`.
3. **`getOrNull` only at true boundaries.** DOM attributes, JSON body, Supabase insert/update, and third-party API contracts. Never in the middle of business logic.
4. **No `getOrNull(x) ?? undefined`.** Use `Option.getOrUndefined(x)` instead.
5. **No `Option.fromNullable(x) → immediate match/getOrElse`.** If you have a nullable value and want to branch, use a plain ternary or `??`. Reserve `Option.fromNullable` for *storing* the value as an Option.
6. **No Option for private mutable refs.** `useRef<T | null>(null)` is correct for timers, DOM refs, and staleness-tracking refs. Use Option only for refs that cross component boundaries or are part of derived state.
7. **Use `Option.all` to flatten.** When combining multiple Options, use `Option.all([a, b])` + `Option.map` or `Option.flatMap`. Never nest `Option.match` inside `Option.match`.

## Patterns

```ts
// ✅ Domain logic: match for value production
const label = Option.match(titleOpt, {
  onNone: () => "Untitled",
  onSome: (t) => t,
});

// ✅ Imperative side-effect: whenSome
whenSome(sessionIdOpt, (id) => router.push(`/${id}`));

// ✅ Boundary: getOrNull for DB/JSON write
const insertRow = { title: Option.getOrNull(titleOpt) };

// ✅ Boundary: getOrUndefined for optional JS property
const viewport = Option.getOrUndefined(viewportOpt);

// ✅ Store setter: accept Option
setCurrentSessionId(Option.some(id));
setEvaluateAction(Option.none());

// ✅ Combining multiple Options
pipe(
  Option.all([originOpt, hostOpt]),
  Option.map(([origin, host]) => new URL(origin).host === host),
  Option.getOrElse(() => false)
);

// ❌ getOrNull in logic (not a boundary)
const title = Option.getOrNull(titleOpt); // wrong — use getOrElse

// ❌ getOrNull ?? undefined
Option.getOrNull(x) ?? undefined; // wrong — use getOrUndefined(x)

// ❌ fromNullable → immediate match (round-trip)
Option.match(Option.fromNullable(data), { ... }); // wrong — use data ? ... : ...

// ❌ Option.match for imperative no-op
Option.match(opt, { onNone: () => {}, onSome: fn }); // wrong — use whenSome(opt, fn)

// ❌ Either.match for imperative no-op
Either.match(either, { onLeft: () => {}, onRight: fn }); // wrong — use whenRight(either, fn)

// ❌ Option for private mutable ref
useRef<Option.Option<Timer>>(Option.none()); // wrong — use useRef<Timer | null>(null)

// ❌ Nested Option.match
Option.match(a, { onSome: () => Option.match(b, ...) }); // wrong — use Option.all
```
